    <h1>Etsy</h1><div id="preamble">
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p><a href="https://www.etsy.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Etsy</a> is an American online market focused on handmade and vintage items.</p>
</div>
<h5 id="_note" class="discrete">Note</h5>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The term “Etsy” is a trademark of Etsy, Inc. This application uses the Etsy API but is not endorsed or certified by Etsy, Inc.</p>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock important">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-important" title="Important"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">Installing the Etsy plugin</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The interface to Etsy is integrated via a <a href="https://marketplace.plentymarkets.com/en/plugins/sales/marktplaetze/etsy_4689" target="_blank" rel="noopener">plugin</a>. Download the Etsy plugin in the plentyMarketplace in order to use it.</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="100">1. Registering with Etsy</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>In order to set up Etsy in your plentymarkets system, you have to register as a Etsy seller first.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="200">2. Installing the Etsy plugin in plentymarkets</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>After buying the Etsy plugin in the plentyMarketplace, install the market in the <strong>Plugins » Plugin overview</strong> menu. Select the filter <strong>Not installed</strong> or <strong>All</strong> to display plugins that have not yet been installed. For further information about downloading and installing plugins, see <a href="/en/plugins/adding-plugins-system#marketplace-plugins">Adding plugins to the system</a>.</p>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="250">2.1. Activating the interface</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>First, the interface has to be activated in the <strong>Setup » Markets » Etsy » Authentication</strong> menu. This is to grant plentymarkets access to your Etsy account.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Activating the interface:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Setup » Markets » Etsy » Authentication</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the globe icon (<span class="icon green"><i class="fa fa-globe  "></i></span>).<br>
→ A new window opens and you are forwarded to Etsy.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Enter your Etsy access data.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Allow access</strong>.<br>
→ The interface to Etsy is activated and you can carry out further settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="300">2.2. Setting up Etsy in plentymarkets</h3>
<div class="admonitionblock important">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-important" title="Important"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">Pay attention to the Renewal options at Etsy</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Prior to setting up Etsy in plentymarkets, you have to set the setting <strong>Renewal options</strong> to <strong>Manual</strong> in the <strong>Shop-Manager » Listings »</strong> <em>Open listing</em> menu at Etsy. Otherwise, the Etsy plugin will not work correctly.</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Go to <strong>Setup » Markets » Etsy » Settings</strong> to activate the data exchange.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Activating the data exchange:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Setup » Markets » Etsy » Settings</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>In the <strong>Processes</strong> area, activate the <strong>Item export</strong>, <strong>Stock update</strong>, and <strong>Order import</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> (<span class="icon green"><i class="fa fa-save  "></i></span>) the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
<h5 id="_setting_up_export_languages" class="discrete">Setting up export languages</h5>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>In the <strong>Export languages</strong> area, you carry out settings for export languages. The <strong>Shop language</strong> is exported by default. Other languages are used for translations of your offers.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Setting up export languages:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Setup » Markets » Etsy » Settings</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select the languages that your offers should be translated into. Available languages are <strong>English</strong>, <strong>German</strong>, and <strong>French</strong>.<br>
<strong><em>Note:</em></strong> The defined <strong>Shop language</strong> is exported by default.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> (<span class="icon green"><i class="fa fa-save  "></i></span>) the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="400">3. Activating the order referrer</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>An order referrer tags an order with the sales channel on which the order was generated. You also need to activate the order referrer in order to link items, characteristics etc. with Etsy. Go to <strong>Setup » Orders » Order referrer</strong> to activate the order referrer.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Activating the order referrer for Etsy:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Setup » Orders » Order referrer</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Activate the option <strong>Etsy</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> (<span class="icon green"><i class="fa fa-save  "></i></span>) the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="500">4. Setting the variation availability</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>You need to activate all variations that you want to sell on Etsy. This is done in the <strong>Availability</strong> tab of a variation within the <strong>Item » Edit item »</strong> <em>Open item</em> <strong>» Tab: Variation ID</strong> menu.</p>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock tip">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-tip" title="Tip"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">Use group function or batch processing</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>You can edit the availability of several variations at once by using either the <a href="/en/item/managing-items#100">variation group function</a> or <a href="/en/item/managing-items#400">batch processing</a>.</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Setting the variation availability for Etsy:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Item » Edit item »</strong> <em>Open item</em> <strong>» Tab: Variation ID » Tab: Settings</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Open the variation that you want to sell on Etsy.<br>
<strong><em>Tip:</em></strong> To sell all variations of an item on Etsy, carry out the settings for the item’s main variation. This activates the availability of all variations of the item.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>In the <strong>Availability</strong> area, activate the option <strong>Active</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the <strong>Availability</strong> tab.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>In the <strong>Markets</strong> area, click in the selection field.<br>
→ A list of all available markets is displayed.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Activate the option <strong>Etsy</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Add</strong> (<span class="icon green"><i class="fa fa-plus-square  "></i></span>).<br>
→ The market is added.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> (<span class="icon green"><i class="fa fa-save  "></i></span>) the settings.<br>
→ The variation is available for Etsy.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="550">5. Saving existing Etsy listing IDs</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>If you already sell a variation on Etsy, save the Etsy listing ID as an SKU for the referrer <strong>Etsy</strong>. By doing so, variations will be assigned to the variations already listed on Etsy during the item export. This is to prevent overselling.<br></p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Saving an Etsy listing-ID:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Item » Edit item »</strong> <em>Open item</em> <strong>» Tab: Variation ID » Tab: Settings</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the <strong>Availability</strong> tab.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>In the <strong>SKU</strong> area, click on <strong>Add</strong> (<span class="icon green"><i class="fa fa-plus-square  "></i></span>).<br>
→ The <strong>New SKU</strong> window opens.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select the referrer <strong>Etsy</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Enter the <strong>SKU</strong> in the following format:<br>
<em>[Etsy listing ID]</em>-<em>[plentymarkets variation ID]</em><br>
<strong><em>Example:</em></strong> 708093072-3467</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Enter the <strong>Parent SKU</strong> in the following format:<br>
<em>[Etsy Listing-ID]</em><br>
<strong><em>Example:</em></strong> 708093072</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Add</strong> (<span class="icon green"><i class="fa fa-plus-square  "></i></span>).<br>
→ The SKU is saved and displayed.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="600">6. Defining a sales price</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Proceed as described below to define a sales price for the order referrer Etsy. This price is displayed on Etsy.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Defining a sales price for Etsy:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Setup » Item » Sales prices »</strong> <em>Open sales price</em> <strong>» Tab: Settings</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Activate the referrer <strong>Etsy</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> (<span class="icon green"><i class="fa fa-save  "></i></span>) the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="900">7. Setting up the item export</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Item data is exported to Etsy via catalogues. The marketplace format <strong>Listing - Etsy</strong> creates a catalogue for exporting data for all Etsy product categories.</p>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="700">7.1. Creating a catalogue</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Item data is exported to Etsy via catalogue using the marketplace format <strong>Listing - Etsy</strong>. Create a catalogue in the <strong>Data » Catalogue</strong> menu to export your items to Etsy. Link the Etsy data fields with item data saved in plentymarkets in the marketplace format afterwards. The catalogue data is automatically exported to Etsy once a day if you have activated the <strong>Item export</strong> in the <strong>Setup » Markets » Etsy » Settings</strong> menu. Is this your first time working with catalogues? Then read up on the basic principle of <a href="#en/data/exporting-data/managing-catalogues">catalogues first</a>.</p>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock tip">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-tip" title="Tip"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
You can create only one catalogue for Etsy. Multiple catalogues are currently not supported for Etsy.
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Creating a catalogue:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Data » Catalogues</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Create catalogue</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Enter a name for the catalogue.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>In the drop-down list <strong>Export type</strong>, select the option <strong>Listing - Etsy</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>In the drop-down list <strong>Format type</strong>, select the option <strong>Item</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>In the drop-down list <strong>Format</strong>, select a category of the marketplace.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> (<span class="icon green"><i class="fa fa-save  "></i></span>) the settings.<br>
→ The catalogue is created.<br>
→ The catalogue is opened for editing.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="map-data-fields">7.2. Mapping data fields in the catalogue</h3>
<div class="admonitionblock important">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-important" title="Important"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">Notes for the Etsy marketplace format</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The <strong>Shop sections</strong> data field in the <strong>Listing - Etsy</strong> template provides all shop sections that you created at Etsy. The shop sections can be selected from the drop-down list and can be linked to data saved in plentymarkets.</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>After you have created a catalogue, map the market’s data fields to item data saved in plentymarkets. Check the documentation of the sales channel to find out what data the market expects for the individual data fields.</p>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock tip">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-tip" title="Tip"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">Using properties</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Use <a href="/en/item/managing-items#3000">properties</a> to export values for data fields that have no corresponding item data saved in plentymarkets.</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Mapping data fields in the catalogue:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Data » Catalogues</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the catalogue.<br>
→ The <strong>Mapping</strong> tab with the market data fields opens.<br>
→ In the left-hand column, the market’s data fields are listed.<br>
<strong><em>Tip:</em></strong> Mandatory fields are flagged with an asterisk (*).</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>To the right of the first marketplace data field, click on <strong>Add data field</strong>.<br>
→ To the left, the plentymarkets data fields are listed in groups.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on a group to expand the associated data fields.<br>
→ The data fields are shown.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Next to the data field you want to select, click on the plus.<br>
→ The data field is added to the view.<br>
<strong><em>Tip:</em></strong> Do you want to export a fixed value for every variation for one of the market data fields? Click on the plus next to <strong>Own value</strong>.<br>
→ The field for the own value is added to the view.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Enter a value into the input field.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the X to close the editing mode.<br>
→ The data field is mapped.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong><em>Optional:</em></strong> Do you want to export two or more plentymarkets fields for a single marketplace data field?</p>
<div class="olist loweralpha">
<ol class="loweralpha" type="a">
<li>
<p>To the right of the data field you just mapped, click on <strong>Add data field</strong> (<span class="icon "><i class="fa fa-link fa-rotate-90 "></i></span>).</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Map an additional plentymarkets data field to the marketplace data field as described above.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>To the right of the column, click on <strong>Settings</strong> (<span class="icon "><i class="fa fa-cog  "></i></span>).</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select a separator from the drop-down list <strong>Separator</strong> or add a custom separator.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings.<br>
→ The additional data field is mapped. During the export, the content of the two plentymarkets data fields is combined and exported as one field.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong><em>Optional:</em></strong> Click on <strong>Add fallback data field</strong> to select a data field that is exported in case another one is not available or empty. You can also add more than one fallback data field.<br>
<strong><em>Note:</em></strong> Even if you assign a fallback data field to a market data field, only one value is exported. The fields are checked in the order in which you mapped them. This means that if the first data field does not provide a value, the first fallback data field is exported etc.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Repeat this mapping for all data fields of the market that you want to export.<br>
<strong><em>Note:</em></strong> All fields flagged with asterisks (*) are mandatory and must be mapped to a plentymarkets data field.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> (<span class="icon green"><i class="fa fa-save  "></i></span>) the settings.<br>
→ The mappings are saved.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="800">8. Updating Etsy categories</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>In order to update Etsy categories in plentymarkets, delete your credentials in the <strong>Setup » Markets » Etsy » Authentication</strong> menu and add them again.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Updating Etsy categories:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Setup » Markets » Etsy » Authentication</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Delete</strong> to delete the credentials.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the globe icon (<span class="icon green"><i class="fa fa-globe  "></i></span>) to add new credentials.<br>
→ You are forwarded to Etsy.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Allow access</strong> at Etsy.<br>
→ New credentials are created and saved in plentymarkets.<br>
→ The Etsy categories are updated.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="900">9. Transferring legal information</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>In order to transfer legal information to Etsy, you have to save the information for each language you use for Etsy. The legal information is then added to the item description.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Saving legal information:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Setup » Markets » Etsy » Legal information</strong>.<br>
→ The window <strong>Legal information</strong> opens.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select the language in which you want to save legal information.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Enter the text.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> (<span class="icon green"><i class="fa fa-save  "></i></span>) the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="1000">10. Automatically sending payment confirmations</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Set up an <a href="/en/automation/event-procedures">event procedure</a> to automatically send payment confirmations to Etsy when incoming payment is booked.</p>
</div>
<div class="openblock collapseBox">
<div class="title">Setting up an event procedure</div>
<div class="content">
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Setup » Orders » Events</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Add event procedure</strong> (<span class="icon green"><i class="fa fa-plus-square  "></i></span>).<br>
→ The <strong>Create new event procedure</strong> window opens.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Enter a distinct name for the event procedure.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select the <strong>event</strong> according to <a href="#etsy-payment-confirmation">Table 1</a>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> (<span class="icon green"><i class="fa fa-save  "></i></span>) the settings.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Carry out the settings according to <a href="#etsy-payment-confirmation">Table 1</a>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Place a check mark next to the option <strong>Active</strong> (<span class="icon blue"><i class="fa fa-check-square  "></i></span>).</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> (<span class="icon green"><i class="fa fa-save  "></i></span>) the settings.<br></p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
</div>
